definitions.definition: A form of redox reaction in which part of a reactant is oxidized and part of it is reduced simultaneously
A reaction wherein a single reactant generates two chemical species which are different from each other and the initial reactant.

main_definition: ( chemistry ) A form of redox reaction in which part of a reactant is oxidized and part of it is reduced simultaneously
